comments.message:
You can't use `record_handle_from_pdr` until you've established that `pldm_msgbuf_extract_uint32()` has correctly extracted a value into it. If you wish to interleave your `EXPECT_*()` calls with the extraction like this, you need to do:

```
rc = pldm_msgbuf_extract_uint32(buf, &record_handle_from_pdr);
ASSERT_EQ(rc, 0);
EXPECT_EQ(record_handle_from_pdr, 10u);
```

However, that will get tedious. I suggest you do all your extractions up front, followed by an `ASSERT_EQ(pldm_msgbuf_validate(buf), 0);` and then a batch of `EXPECT_*()`s.

Please fix this throughout.
